Looking across the Pantheon you’ve built over many conversations, I’d make the Spy less of a standalone daemon and more of a horizontal sensing layer. It doesn’t own many outputs itself—it improves the inputs to everyone else.

Here’s how I’d integrate it.

Daemon	Spy contributes	Spy receives
Spider	New nodes, hidden relationships, unexplored domains	Relationship maps showing where to scout next
Raven	Emerging stories worth communicating	Public reactions and feedback
Checksum	Candidate hypotheses to verify	Confidence scores and corrections
Mimic	External patterns worth studying	Reconstructed behavioral models
Herding Dog	Where attention is drifting or concentrating	Signals about successful guidance
Pinecone	Dormant ideas whose time hasn’t come	Seeds ready for reactivation
Flood Eater	Early warning of information overload	Cleaned information channels
Scarab	Valuable waste, abandoned projects, forgotten ideas	Recycled concepts worth investigating
Farmer	Fertile communities and opportunities	Reports on growth and adoption
Architect	Requirements gathered from reality	New structures to explore
Theory Group	Interesting anomalies	Better models for observation
Simulation Lab	Real-world scenarios to test	Predictions that improve reconnaissance

